# Trading Journal — Cursor Rules
# These rules are enforced across the entire codebase.

## React & Next.js

- Server Components by default. Add `"use client"` only when using hooks, browser APIs, or event handlers.
- Never use `useEffect` purely to fetch data in client components — prefer React Server Components or pass data as props.
- `useCallback` and `useMemo` only when you can demonstrate a performance need. Premature memoization is dead weight.
- Pages are thin coordinators — business logic belongs in hooks or `lib/`.
- Never fetch data directly inside a component body at the module level — use `useEffect` with proper deps or RSC.

## Components

- Max 200 lines per component file. Split anything longer.
- One component per file.
- Props are always typed with an interface, never inline type literals.
- No prop named `data` — be specific: `trades`, `account`, `playbook`.
- Event handler props are named `on[Noun][Verb]`: `onTradeCreate`, `onAccountSelect`, `onFilterChange`.
- Components live in the most specific directory:
  - `components/ui/` — headless primitives and design-system atoms
  - `components/trade/` — trade-specific UI
  - `components/dashboard/` — dashboard-specific widgets
  - `components/journal/` — journal editor components
  - `components/layout/` — structural layout (sidebar, header)
  - `components/prop-firm/` — prop firm components

## Styling

- No inline `style={{}}` objects unless the value is truly dynamic and cannot be expressed in Tailwind.
- No hardcoded hex colors or Tailwind color literals for semantic colors (profit, loss, accent). Use CSS variables.
  - Profit / positive: `text-[var(--profit-primary)]` or `var(--profit-primary)` in SVG/Recharts
  - Loss / negative: `text-[var(--loss-primary)]` or `var(--loss-primary)` in SVG/Recharts
  - Accent: `var(--accent-primary)`
  - Text: `var(--text-primary)`, `var(--text-secondary)`, `var(--text-tertiary)`
  - Borders: `var(--border-default)`, `var(--border-subtle)`
  - Surfaces: `var(--surface-elevated)`, `var(--surface-hover)`, `var(--surface-active)`
- Sidebar width: always `var(--sidebar-width)` from globals.css. Never hardcode `240px` or `280px`.
- Use Tailwind spacing scale only. No `px-[17px]` arbitrary values.
- No dynamic Tailwind class generation like `` `grid-cols-${n}` `` — JIT cannot scan these. Use inline style for computed values.

## TypeScript

- No `any` type. Use `unknown` if the type is genuinely unknown, then narrow with a type guard.
- No `as any` casts. Fix the underlying type instead.
- No `// @ts-ignore` or `// eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any`. Fix the type.
- All API response data validated with Zod before use in business logic.
- No `JSON.parse()` without a surrounding `try-catch` and Zod validation of the result.
- String literal unions for finite sets — prefer `'LONG' | 'SHORT'` over plain `string` for direction fields.

## Dead Code

- No commented-out code. Remove it.
- No `console.log`, `console.warn`, `console.error` in components or `lib/` files.
- No placeholder functions that do nothing and return nothing.
- No `// TODO` comments that are older than the current sprint. Fix it or file an issue.
- No import that is not used.

## Hardcoded Values — Zero Tolerance

- No magic numbers. Every numeric constant must be a named export from `lib/constants/`.
- No magic strings for routes — import from `lib/constants/routes.ts`.
- No magic strings for feature states — use a typed union or enum.
- API keys and secrets in environment variables only — never in source.
- Sidebar width → `SIDEBAR_WIDTH` from `lib/constants/app.ts`.
- Breakpoints → `MOBILE_BREAKPOINT_PX` from `lib/constants/app.ts`.
- Auto-save delay → `AUTOSAVE_DEBOUNCE_MS` from `lib/constants/app.ts`.

## Duplicate Logic — Zero Tolerance

- Prop account filter query logic lives only in `lib/utils/query-helpers.ts → withPropAccountFilter()`.
- Currency/number formatters live only in `lib/utils/format.ts`.
- P&L and direction color logic lives only in `lib/utils/trade-colors.ts`.
- Date range helpers live only in `lib/utils/date-range.ts`.
- Chart color constants live only in `lib/constants/chart-colors.ts`.
- Any time you copy-paste a block of 3 or more lines, extract a function.

## Backend / API Routes

- Every route: authenticate first → authorize → validate input with Zod → process.
- All inputs validated with Zod before use. Never trust request body shape.
- All responses follow the shape: `{ data?, error?, message? }`.
- No `console.log` debug statements.
- Rate limiting applied to all AI and expensive endpoints via `lib/utils/rate-limit.ts`.
- Service role Supabase client (`createAdminClient`) only for operations that require bypassing RLS. Never expose service role key to client.

## File Naming

- Pages: `page.tsx` (Next.js convention)
- Components: `kebab-case.tsx`
- Hooks: `use-kebab-case.ts`
- Utilities: `kebab-case.ts`
- Types: `kebab-case.ts`
- Constants: `kebab-case.ts`

## Imports

- Import order: external packages → `@/lib/` → `@/hooks/` → `@/components/` → relative
- Use `@/` alias for all non-relative imports within `src/`.
- No barrel re-exports that only re-export a single item — import directly.
